{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"func","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"fileTest","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"test"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV","text":"FileTest","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Function","externalID":"s:4GLib8fileTest8filename4testSbSPys4Int8VGSg_AA04FileC0VtF","title":"fileTest(filename:test:)"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/fileTest(filename:test:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if any of the tests in the bitfield "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"test"},{"text":" are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, ","type":"text"},{"code":"(G_FILE_TEST_EXISTS | G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" if the file exists; the check whether it’s a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"directory doesn’t matter since the existence test is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". With"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the current set of available tests, there’s no point passing in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"more than one test at a time."}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/filetest(filename:test:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fileTest","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"test","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"FileTest","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/FileTest","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apart from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"type":"text","text":" all tests follow symbolic links,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"so for a symbolic link to a regular file ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_file_test()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will return"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" for both "},{"code":"isSymlink","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isRegular"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note, that for a dangling symbolic link "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_test()"},{"text":" will return","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":" for all other flags."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You should never use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_test()"},{"text":" to test whether it is safe","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to perform an operation, because there is always the possibility"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the condition changing before you actually perform the operation,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, you might think you could use "},{"code":"isSymlink","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to know whether it is safe to write to a file without being"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"tricked into writing into a different location. It doesn’t work!","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"(C Language Example):","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"C","type":"codeListing","code":[" \/\/ DON'T DO THIS"," if (!g_file_test (filename, G_FILE_TEST_IS_SYMLINK))","   {","     fd = g_open (filename, O_WRONLY);","     \/\/ write to fd","   }",""," \/\/ DO THIS INSTEAD"," fd = g_open (filename, O_WRONLY | O_NOFOLLOW | O_CLOEXEC);"," if (fd == -1)","   {","     \/\/ check error","     if (errno == ELOOP)","       \/\/ file is a symlink and can be ignored","     else","       \/\/ handle errors as before","   }"," else","   {","     \/\/ write to fd","   }"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Another thing to note is that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exists"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"isExecutable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" are implemented using the ","type":"text"},{"code":"access()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"system call. This usually doesn’t matter, but if your program"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is setuid or setgid it means that these tests will give you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the answer for the real user ID and group ID, rather than the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"effective user ID and group ID.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows, there are no symlinks, so testing for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isSymlink"},{"text":" will always return ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Testing for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isExecutable"},{"type":"text","text":" will just check that the file exists and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"its name indicates that it is executable, checking for well-known"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"extensions and those listed in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PATHEXT","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" environment variable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/fileTest(filename:test:)":{"type":"topic","title":"fileTest(filename:test:)","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if any of the tests in the bitfield "},{"code":"test","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". For example, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(G_FILE_TEST_EXISTS | G_FILE_TEST_IS_DIR)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"will return ","type":"text"},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if the file exists; the check whether it’s a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"directory doesn’t matter since the existence test is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":". With","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the current set of available tests, there’s no point passing in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"more than one test at a time.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/filetest(filename:test:)","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/fileTest(filename:test:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"fileTest"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"test","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"FileTest","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib8FileTestV"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/glib","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/FileTest":{"title":"FileTest","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"A test to perform on a file using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_file_test()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"FileTest","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"FileTest","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/FileTest","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/filetest","kind":"symbol"},"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use":{"url":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","identifier":"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Time-of-check_to_time-of-use","type":"link","title":"TOCTOU","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"TOCTOU","type":"text"}]}}}